# Handoff and git

- Before handoff, inspect `git diff` and verify only task-scoped files changed.
- Format only touched handwritten code according to `.editorconfig` and nearby style.
  No repository formatter is currently configured; do not invent one or reformat broadly.
- For changed C#, check missing/duplicate `using` directives, asmdef references,
  runtime/editor boundaries, generated-file status, and serialized field compatibility.
- For Unity assets, verify paired `.meta` handling. For submodules, verify no unintended
  nested changes or pointer updates.
- Run proportionate available checks. Unity tests require Unity; do not substitute
  `dotnet test`.
- Report checks actually run and any verification not run.
- Never commit unless explicitly asked. Never push unless explicitly asked.
- Do not update git config, skip hooks, force-push, hard-reset, or discard user changes.
- Review diffs skeptically after implementation; prioritize correctness, compatibility,
  serialization, resource lifetime, and package boundaries over style nits.
